message: >-
  If you use this whitepaper in academic or industry publications, please cite
  it as below. For the underlying software citation, see the companion code
  repository at https://github.com/baiyuan-tech/pif.
title: >-
  PIF AI Whitepaper: A Multi-Tenant AI-Assisted Platform for Cosmetic
  Product Information File Documentation Under Taiwan's Cosmetic Hygiene
  and Safety Act
abstract: >-
  Technical whitepaper describing PIF AI, an open-source multi-tenant SaaS
  platform that uses Anthropic Claude (via the Claude API and developed
  with Claude Code), automated toxicology database queries
  (PubChem, TFDA restricted/prohibited lists, ECHA, OECD), and a central
  RAG service to reduce Taiwan-regulated cosmetic Product Information File
  (PIF) documentation from 4–8 weeks to 3–5 business days, with an online
  Safety Assessor (SA) review and electronic signature workflow. Covers
  regulatory background, system architecture, AI engine design, toxicology
  pipeline, the RAG isolation model (Scheme C+), security threat model,
  SA workflow, deployment, and open-source strategy.
